post_text:
Dear Families,

Southern California Edison may initiate power outages at each of our school sites. When and if these happen, our school offices may need to close in the afternoon. In the event of the offices closing due to a power outage, please call the District Office at 564-8081 to let us know your needs and we will communicate with the school sites who will return your call as soon as they can. The school offices will reopen at 7:30 the next morning.

Southern California Edison puede iniciar cortes de energía temporales en cada una de nuestras escuelas. Cuando esto ocurra y si esto sucede, es posible que las oficinas de nuestra escuela cierren por la tarde. En el caso de que las oficinas cierren debido a un corte de energía, llame a la Oficina del Distrito al 564-8081 para informarnos sus necesidades y nos comunicaremos con las escuelas que le devolverán la llamada lo antes posible. Las oficinas de la escuela volverán a abrir a las 7:30 de la mañana siguiente. Como siempre, toda la información se puede encontrar en nuestro sitio web.

Thank you,
Laura A. Gonzalez, Superintendent

Castle Rock Elementary School
August 7 at 2:06 PM ·

ATTENTION WILDCAT FAMILIES!!!
We are excited to announce to all of you that we will be hosting a Castle Rock Elementary School Meet & Greet Pick Up Party on 08/11/2020
We have set up a schedule for you to drop by the campus. You will have the opportunity to turn in your registration packets, meet your child's teacher, pick up a distance learning instructional schedule, take home some materials and check out a chrome book. Don't forget to bring an empty backpack because we have lots of stuff for you to take home. We are even providing an opportunity for you to take that 1st day of school picture that we all can't live without.
We can't wait to see you and our students even if it's while we are all wearing masks and at least 6 feet apart!

Hello Woodlake Families.

We are preparing to serve meals to all children 1-18 years of age Monday, April 27th and Wednesday, April 29th, between 11:00 and 12:30pm. All meals will be distributed at F.J. White Learning Center, Castle Rock, Woodlake High School, and now our Central Kitchen location 355 S. Acacia directly across the street from Dryvit.

Please stay indoors as much as possible, limit contact with others and continue washing your hands often. Check in with your child’s teacher regarding any work that your children should be doing. Students in grades 3-12 are receiving notices online by their teachers so they should check email daily.

Thank you.

Hola Familias de Woodlake,
Soy la señora Gonzalez, la Superintendente del Distrito Unificado de las Escuelas de Woodlake.
Les quiero informar que por hoy la distribución de alimentos ha sido cancelada. Volveremos a servir alimentos tan pronto como nos sea posible. Esperamos que ustedes estén bien y que se estén quedando en casa tanto como le sea posible.

Esto incluye el juego limitado con otros estudiantes. Como ustedes ya saben, el virus se desparrama rápidamente y es importante mantenerse informado, quedarse dentro de casa y continuar lavándose las manos seguido.

También, revise con el maestro/a de su hijo/a acerca de cualquier trabajo que debe estar realizando. Los estudiantes están recibiendo notificaciones por línea de parte de sus maestros/as. Por favor déjele saber a sus hijos/as que los extrañamos y que queremos que continúen realizando lo mejor.

Gracias por su paciencia.
Nos sentimos confidentes de que saldremos de esto juntos.
Laura A. Gonzalez, Superintendent

post_text:
Buenas tardes familias de Woodlake. Soy Laura Gonzalez, la Superintendente de las escuelas de Woodlake Unified.

En las Escuelas Unificadas de Woodlake, comprendemos nuestro compromiso de servir como una “línea vital” para nuestra comunidad entera. Nuestro equipo Unificado de Woodlake se levantara y trabajaran juntos para contribuir al Espíritu Humanitario que está vivo en Woodlake, California.

Nos estamos preparando para comenzar a servir alimentos a todos los niños de entre 0-18 años de edad para mañana, Jueves 19 de Marzo. Todos los alimentos serán distribuidos en las paradas de autobuses, y las escuelas F. J. White, Castle Rock, y en frente de la escuela Secundaria de Woodlake. Un adulto no tiene que acompañar al niño/a.

Gracias.

A message from Woodlake Unified School District,
Due to the current circumstances causing students to remain at home, if you have an At-Home Student internet device that is not working, you can bring it to the District office for it to be repaired or replaced. We are available to help you from 7:00 AM to 4:00 PM. For more information, please call 564-8081 x8901.

Thank you.

Un aviso de Distrito Escolar Unificado de Woodlake,
Debido a las circunstancias actuales que hacen que los estudiantes permanezcan en casa, si tiene un dispositivo de Internet para estudiantes en el hogar que no funciona, puede llevarlo a la oficina del distrito para que lo reparen o reemplacen. Estamos disponibles para ayudarlo de 7:00 a.m. a 4:00 p.m. Para obtener más información, llame al 564-8081 x8901.

Gracias.

Good afternoon.

With all that our students are exposed to through the news outlets and adult conversations, please have a conversation with your children about the importance of not using the COVID-19 (Coronavirus) as a joke. You might have heard that a student made an announcement in class which has been investigated and found untrue. These tall tales so to speak can cause unnecessary panic in our schools and community.

Thank you for your assistance.

Laura A. Gonzalez
Superintendent

Job Summary
CLASSIFIED POSITION:
• Bravo Lake High School/Woodlake Community Day School – Grades: 7-12
• Salary: Range 10 ($13.29-$14.73 per hour - placement dependent upon like experience)
• Annual Number of Work Days: 8 hours per day/184 days per year
• Time: 6:30 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. (30 minutes lunch) - Instructional Aide III (7hrs)/Custodian (1hr)
• 2019/2020 School Year

QUALIFICATIONS:
• High School Diploma or equivalent; AA degree or at least 48 college units or passing score on the TCOE Instructional Aide Assessment Test;
• Valid CA driver license and proof of insurance,
• Effective computer, communication, and organizational skills;
• Ability to carry out oral/written directions, work collaboratively with students and content area teachers;
• Ability to effectively translate oral/written text between English and Spanish;
• Spanish speaking preferred but not required.
• May transport students within the school district

Woodlake Unified School District has an opening for an Attendance/Health Clerk at Woodlake High School.

Requirements/Qualifications:
High School Diploma or equivalent; Passing score on District Proficiency Test (will not be required if applicant has at least 48 college units or an Associate degree or higher – must submit college transcripts as proof) and District Computer Test; Valid CPR/First Aid Certification or willing to obtain if hired;

Effective computer, communication, and organizational skills; Ability to fulfill essential job functions noted in position description; Possess effective ability to work collaboratively and provide professional/courteous customer service in all contacts and interactions.

Spanish speaking required.

Deadline to apply is: January 22, 2020 at 4:30 p.m.

Please apply at www.edjoin.org/w-usd or pick up an application at 300 W. Whitney Ave., Woodlake, CA 93286.
